< Review>
Short version : Very poor food quality(later hours at least)

I went there at around 9:50 PM, got some orange chicken, mushroom chicken and Chow mein. Was so hungry that I had the entree of orange chicken in the parking lot. The smell, or should I say fumes, from it made me cough. After my coughing fit was done (not ashmatic) I ate a piece to find that it tasted a lot like McDonald's chicken mcnuggets. Chow mein was dry and flavorless. Would get my money back, but I already drove home, hoping the entree was just a fluke. It wasn't. Definitely do not recommend, at least not in the later hours. Can't say for mid day. (On a side note, when I got home, I opened the tray to find the spot for the mushroom chicken was completely empty, almost clean. The entree was just with the noodles...
Panda Express, if you read this, I would very greatly appreciate a refund, or at the very least a replacement meal of decent quality. Thank you for reading.< /Review>

Aman Mehrzai< /Name>
< Text>
Big let down as Panda Express was a place I really enjoyed. The best thing about this place was the service and cleanliness, which earns it two stars. The food however, needs work. Perhaps it was because I was there in the evening, but still it was pretty bad. I was craving the walnut shrimp for weeks. I was already irked that the server said there was a 7 shrimp count per serving (although not her fault I suppose, just following management orders). I ordered a double portion for my wife and I just to make sure there was enough. I counted them when I got home out of curiosity. They shorted me two and threw in a few broken walnuts. Considering they up charged me $1.75 extra for ordering shrimp I expect better. To top it off the shrimp batter was stale lacking glaze. Again, maybe it was the end of the day syndrome or just a bad location but I will unfortunately not be going to PE for a while. Too many options in the area.<//Text>

Casual, friendly, retro-50's-to-60's bar, in Old--town Goleta. Generous selection of craft beers. If you prefer a "hoppy" brew, or double-chocolate stout, the barkeeps will steer you right. <Text>How do you describe this funky and rad Old Town Goleta favorite?  It's like the best beer tasting you've been too at the most perfect venue you can imagine. Okay, maybe that's a bit much, but it is by far my favorite Goleta watering hole. They have about 10 amazing beers on tap that rotate often.  They have over 30 eclectic bottles to choose from. <username>Tiffanie Lai</username><time>1570335497256< /time>< rate>
5<//rate>
<Review>Temescal also has a Master's team.  This pool has the most lap swim hours in the City of Oakland city pools between Master's hours + city lap swim hours.

Pool is 33 yards long and is roughly 79-80 degrees Fahrenheit.

Times of lap swim does change seasonally, so be sure to check the City of Oakland official website before heading over.

Please note, this pool is a chlorinated pool and not saline treated. (Fun fact, public entities are required to use a chemical disinfectant as a primary source of disinfectant. It's part of county health code.)

During the summer the offer a robust list of programs including swim lesson, Jr. Lifeguard, youth recreation swim team, lap swim, and recreation swimming for the community. Staff is usually local young adults that have grown up in the Oakland Parks and Recreation Youth Development program and want to give back in the community!<//Review><pictures>None<//pictures><Resp>None<//Resp><Gmap_id>0x80857de4efe15207:0x67b88596df87a647< /Gmap_id></record>
</dataset><record>

<Review>The finished product exceeds expectations. Chase was polite, communicated clearly, adjusted the size of the Solatube as per my original thoughts and made sure that the location was a good fit with the limitations of the water pipes in the attic. He protected my homes surfaces and carefully placed drop clothes. He cleaned up thoroughly after installation. He explained every step. The only reason for 3 stars is that he inadvertently drilled a hole in my new roof under solar panels. He was not aware that the panels were on the roof and I now will need to have shingles replaced and hopefully will not have to uninstall solar panels to do so. He was very forthcoming about the issue and the company will take care of the invoice for repairs. Once the repairs are complete and invoice covered, I will upgrade my review with additional star(s).

< text>
My family and I moved here from San Jose. In San Jose there are a lot of family owned restaurants that are great. We have a few of our favorites, but when we moved here we noticed the wasn't  that many here in Tracy. I came to Mendoza's with my sister's and mother for the first time ordered the two item plate. It was SO good. I told my husband about this place and he had breakfast there while waiting to get our car fixed. We both agree it's probably the best Mexican Restaurant in Tracy. This place has officially become our favorite place to eat. The only down side is that they close so early, 2pm. There are days we want to go out to eat for dinner, but Mendoza is closed. It's probably better for our pocketbook that they close so early. Lol Nonetheless, highly recommended place and the prices are reasonable, amount of food you get is great (two thumbs up), service is wonderful and that place itself is very clean. If you ever get a chance to fit in dessert, try the Flan...it's homemade and they add something extra too. SUPER delicious. ‚ò∫üëçüëç< /text>

<userid>109083694777525267700< /userid><username>Pablo Juarez</username><Time>1500644708802</Time><Rate>5</Rate><text>I had eggs rancheto style which is very good</text><Pics>None< /Pics><resp>None< /resp>< gmapID>

< Rating>
3< /Rating>
< gmap_id>
0x80903daa16982af9:0x8bfd0787e652a4ff<//gmap_id>
< Text>
The restaurant is clean and you can choose from sitting at the counter or tables by the window.

We were greeted and seated within a reasonable time. ¬†Their menu which was enormous had numerous pictures of the dishes to choose from and was reasonably priced.

The "service" itself was a disappointment for a place that wasn't so busy. ¬†After being seated, we waited 10 minutes just to place our order and another 10 minutes for chips and salsa.

Our main order would take another 20 minutes or so to arrive, which I felt was unacceptable given the small crowd inside.

I noticed only one cook which could account for the slow service. ¬†Everyone had already been served when we entered and were seated.

Although there were two waitresses on the floor, our waitress was more interested in yanking with her coworker who was eating and watching TV then to attend to their customer's needs.

I've had chips and salsa at numerous Mexican themed restaurants but this one was unique in that it included a "warm bean dipping sauce with a sprinkle of cheese (queso fresco)."

There was nothing special about the dip but added a new dimension and flavor. ¬†Their salsa sauce was average and better than some others we have tried around town.

Because of the water shortage here in the state, this place won't serve you water unless you ask for it.

My water arrived with a slice of "wedged lime" which was dry and definitely not fresh.

Honestly, it's little attention to detail, such as making sure the garnish is fresh, goes a long way and says volumes about the your restaurant.

It also sets the stage for what the customers can expect. ¬†In my opinion, I was having second doubts.

I ordered their two plate combo, which was a Chile Relleno and Beef Taco, and also included rice and beans.

My wife ordered the combination special (can't recall the name) which came sizzling hot in a "Pumice" style bowl and arrived steaming hot from the kitchen.

My Chile Relleno was average in taste and the pepper itself wasn't firm but more on the soft side.

The cheese was chewy but overpowering and took away the taste of the pepper. ¬†Next was the beef taco, which was the other part of my combo plate.

I hate to say it but the beef was tough and dried out which for me spoiled the taco experience. ¬†The shell was crispy but slightly on the greasy side.

The rice and refried beans was average in taste and texture, but how can you mess that up?

My wife's plate/bowl came with prawns, cactus, chicken, beef, and vegetables along with rice and beans.

The presentation itself looked appealing but you couldn't touch anything inside of this "lava boiling pot" for several minutes until the bubbling stopped!

The prawns were cooked just right and not overdone to the point where the meat would be too tough to chew.

I've never had cactus which hung loosely around my wife's pumice bowl. ¬†The cactus itself didn't have any "distinct flavor" other than having a lemony taste.

The plant itself was somewhat chewy but is definitely an acquired taste.

Other garnishments included scallions, jalape√±os, and radishes in a tomato based sauce. ¬†Overall, my wife said she enjoyed her meal.

Overall, our experience here was average with the exception of the service which I felt could've used a lot of improvement.

The food didn't stand out but they did give you a lot for the price.

They say that word of mouth is what brings in the customers, but with better service, attention to detail (dried lime on water glass), and better food preparation, this place could gain more "exposure and a following."< /Text>

<Review>Pros: Excellent service here! They are very quick and to the point while still remaining very thorough. The unit I was assigned was also very convenient. It's also very secure.

Cons: Pricing was too expensive for the small 5x10 unit I was using. $55/month with autopay, and my first month wasn't $1 like their promo and reps said it would be. Also, whenever I'd go back there would be a bunch of dust inside my unit from being blown inside from the outside of it. A lot of that dirt got on my bed and on my other belongings, which are very sensitive items.
*Update: Also, my second time here I got a 5x10 unit again, but this time they gave me a worse unit that is very exposed and requires 2 locks that they charged me twice the price for ($40). Totally not fair. The agent on the phone said I only needed 1 lock, but in person they said otherwise. Now I have 3 locks by them that I paid a total of $60 for. Ridiculous how they make their money.

Overall, I would say this place can be okay if you really need to butcher your move. If anyone decides to come here, just be cautious and make sure all of your items are covered and clean at all times. Don't hesitate to confront them about anything and if you have a problem then let them know.</Review>< pictures>
